# Meniscus — Design System

The whole site extends the hero (a glass sheet over deep, viscous water with
slowly blooming ink). Every surface is a sheet of glass suspended over deep
water; content surfaces *through* it (refraction, blur, hairline edges), it
never sits flat *on* it. Instrument-grade, quiet, premium. Empty space is depth
and pressure, not absence. The owner is an engineer of expensive systems
(PCI-DSS payment gateways, database internals) — so the "clearing-house dossier"
persona (mono coordinates, telemetry labels, ledger language) is kept and
refined, not discarded.

**Non-negotiables on every task:** restraint over decoration; 60fps; lazy-load
3D; respect `prefers-reduced-motion`; graceful degradation on weak GPUs; fully
responsive — the premium feel must survive on mobile. When unsure, do less but
make it intentional.

**Hard structural mandate — NOT a single-page scroller.** This is a multi-page
*dossier* (a book / case-file), navigated chapter to chapter — never one long
scroll of everything. The website is itself the work sample (judged by HRs,
CTOs, and engineers), so every route, transition, and interaction is a
deliberate demonstration of craft.

## 0. Narrative — the dossier (read first)

Three audiences, each answered without burying the others: **HR / hiring**
(the person + credentials), **CTOs** (systems depth, scale, ownership), and
**engineers** (technical craft + range).

**Throughline — the spine of the whole site:** *Kamlesh builds software where
being wrong is expensive — and owns it end to end — proven across three
theaters: a fintech gateway at scale, a startup run solo, and database
internals.*

**The book — five chapters, each its own route/page with its own glass+water hero:**

| #  | Chapter         | Route         | Answers      | Core content |
|----|-----------------|---------------|--------------|--------------|
| 00 | Index (cover)   | `/`           | the thesis   | fluid hero + statement + a dossier-style table of contents into the chapters |
| 01 | Production      | `/experience` | CTO          | payment gateway (PCI-DSS L1, €100Ms, Google/Apple Pay, +11%) + Bitnine OSS DB internals |
| 02 | Venture         | `/startup`    | "can he own it" | XSTRYV — sole engineer, 1,600+ users / 250+ companies, end-to-end ownership; + founder community (Slush, UN Millennium) |
| 03 | Lab             | `/projects`   | engineers    | personal projects / technical range; home of the Fish companion (§8) |
| 04 | Profile         | `/about`      | HR           | education (Helsinki MSc 5/5, NUST), skills matrix, certifications, contact |

The landing (`/`) is a **cover + table of contents**, not a content dump — it
sells the throughline and routes each audience to their chapter; chapter depth
lives on the routes. Navigation behaves like **turning pages**: a persistent
numbered chapter index in the header, and a "next chapter →" pager at the foot
of every page. Route transitions (Motion dissolve, §4) are the page turns.

**Content source of truth:** `Curriculum_Vitae_Md.md` (repo root). Reconcile all
`src/data/*` to it — notably the **XSTRYV startup role is missing from the data**
and must be added.

## 1. Aesthetic direction — "Meniscus"

The curved line where water climbs the wall of its glass — the boundary the hero
lives on. Glass, water, depth, refraction, fluidity. The connective tissue
across every section is **depth + refraction**: a single reusable glass surface
treatment so no section ever looks like a different template.

## 2. Color — strict, depth over variety

One base family (deep-water neutrals) + exactly **two** accents drawn from the
hero inks. Two more inks are **functional signal only** (status), never
decoration. Brass is the only warm; Tide is the only cool; everything else is a
neutral or a rare signal. Use color as punctuation.

Dark-first (primary world). Light is a retained "frosted glass" alternate.

```css
/* Base — deep water neutrals (DARK) */
--abyss:   #0a0d12;   /* page floor (hero water = #0c0f14) */
--depth:   #11161d;   /* raised surface */
--shoal:   #19212b;   /* glass panel fill */

/* Ink — text (DARK) */
--trace:   #dde3ea;   /* headings / primary */
--text:    #9aa3ad;   /* body */
--muted:   #6e7681;   /* captions, mono labels */

/* Accents — from the hero inks */
--brass:   #c89b6a;   /* PRIMARY warm — ink signature, primary buttons */
--tide:    #4a86e8;   /* SECONDARY cool — links, data, focus rings */

/* Reserved signal ONLY (never decoration) */
--live:    #e0664a;   /* error / live state */
--graph:   #4fae93;   /* success / positive delta */

/* Glass + refraction */
--glass-sheen: #cfe0ea;
--edge:        rgba(221,227,234,0.10);  /* hairline border */
--edge-strong: rgba(221,227,234,0.18);
```

Light ("frosted glass") counterpart: `--mist #eef1f5` (page, = hero light water),
`--frost #ffffff`, `--haze #f4f2ee`; text `--trace #1a1d22` / `--text #4a5159`;
accents `--brass #8a7048`, `--tide #3568b8`; edges use `rgba(26,29,34,*)`.

Exposed via Tailwind v4 `@theme` → `bg-abyss`, `bg-shoal`, `text-trace`,
`text-brass`, `border-edge`, etc. Theme switches on `[data-theme]` (existing
mechanism in `src/lib/theme.ts` — keep it).

## 3. Type system

Three faces, already loaded — keep them: **Newsreader** (display serif),
**IBM Plex Sans** (body), **IBM Plex Mono** (telemetry/labels). Confident, large,
generous spacing.

| Role            | Face            | Size                          | Detail |
|-----------------|-----------------|-------------------------------|--------|
| Display XL      | Newsreader 400  | `clamp(2.75rem, 7vw, 5rem)`   | `tracking -0.025em`, `lh 1.0` |
| Display L       | Newsreader 400  | `clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3.25rem)` | italic available for emphasis |
| H2 section      | Newsreader 400  | `clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.35rem)` | `lh 1.15`, max `28ch` |
| H3              | Plex Sans 500   | `1.25rem`                     | |
| Lead            | Plex Sans 400   | `17px / 1.55`                 | max `65ch` |
| Body            | Plex Sans 400   | `16px / 1.6`                  | |
| Eyebrow / coords| Plex Mono 500   | `11–13px`                     | `tracking 0.06–0.1em`, lowercase |

Paragraphs cap at `65ch`, headings at `28ch`. Italic Newsreader (+ `--brass`) for
emphasis spans, as in the hero name.

## 4. Motion language — slow, viscous, deliberate

**One rule: Scroll position → GSAP. Interaction & state → Motion.**

- **Lenis** — site-wide smooth scroll, the viscous glide (lerp ≈ `0.08`). Drives
  ScrollTrigger from one rAF loop (`lenis.on('scroll', ScrollTrigger.update)`).
- **GSAP + ScrollTrigger** — anything tied to scroll: section reveals, staggered
  entrances, parallax depth layers, per-route hero transitions. Reveals fire
  **once** (no replay/yo-yo).
- **Motion (Framer Motion)** — anything tied to component state: route page
  transitions (dissolve via `AnimatePresence`), hover/press micro-states, menu
  and theme toggle, layout shifts.

**Feel:**
- Signature easing **`water` = `cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)`** (quick onset →
  long deceleration). Enter variant **`settle` = `cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)`**.
- **No bounce, no back, no elastic, no spring overshoot.** Springs critically damped.
- Durations: hover `200–300ms`; reveals `0.9–1.2s`; route transitions `0.6–0.9s`;
  parallax scrubbed to scroll.
- **Signature reveal — "ink bloom":** `opacity 0→1`, `translateY 24→0`,
  `blur 8px→0` (refraction sharpening), `scale 1.01→1`, stagger `80–120ms`.
- **Depth parallax:** background/water layers drift slower than foreground (5–15%).
- **`prefers-reduced-motion`:** Lenis off (native scroll), reveals become instant
  opacity-only, no blur, no parallax. Always provide this path.

## 5. Spacing & layout — it breathes

- **8pt scale:** `4 · 8 · 12 · 16 · 24 · 32 · 48 · 64 · 96 · 128 · 160`.
- **Section rhythm:** `clamp(120px, 16vh, 200px)` top & bottom. (Old 72px = too tight.)
- **Container:** max `1200px`, gutters `clamp(20px, 5vw, 40px)`.
- **Glass panels:** inner padding `40–56px` desktop; one idea per row; lots of
  `--abyss` around everything.
- **The unifier — reusable glass treatment** on every card/panel:
  `backdrop-blur + saturate`, hairline top highlight, deep soft drop shadow,
  faint inner glow. (Section-level version of the hero's `hero-panel`/`hero-frame`.)

## 6. Routing & layout architecture

Stack: React 19 + Vite + TypeScript, Tailwind v4 (`@theme`), shadcn/ui, GSAP +
ScrollTrigger, Lenis, Framer Motion, React Three Fiber + drei,
`react-router-dom`.

Routes — the five chapters (§0). Each non-cover route gets its own hero in the
same glass+water family:

```
/            00 · Index — cover: fluid hero + statement + chapter index
/experience  01 · Production — work at scale       → own hero (PLACEHOLDER)
/startup     02 · Venture — XSTRYV + founder        → own hero (PLACEHOLDER)
/projects    03 · Lab — personal projects + Fish    → own hero (PLACEHOLDER)
/about       04 · Profile — education, skills, contact
```

Layout tree:

```
main.tsx
└─ <BrowserRouter>
   └─ <SmoothScrollProvider>      // Lenis + ScrollTrigger wiring, reduced-motion aware
      └─ <SiteLayout>             // Header (route-aware nav) + Footer
         └─ <AnimatePresence>     // Motion route dissolve
            ├─ "/"           → <Landing>
            ├─ "/experience" → <ExperiencePage>
            └─ "/startup"    → <StartupPage>
```

Shared primitives (build once, reuse everywhere):
`<Container>`, `<Section>`, `<GlassPanel>`, `<Reveal>` (GSAP scroll wrapper),
`<Eyebrow>` (mono label), a `<RouteHero>` family, plus two book primitives:
`<ChapterIndex>` (the cover's table of contents) and `<ChapterPager>` (the
"next chapter →" foot of each page). Landing uses the existing fluid hero
(`src/hero/fluid`). `/experience`, `/startup`, and `/projects` use clearly-marked
hero placeholders:

```tsx
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    PLACEHOLDER · /experience hero — same glass+water family.
    Drop R3F scene here. Keep <RouteHero> wrapper for layout + scroll.
   ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
```

Landing (`/`) = **cover + table of contents only**: Hero → Index statement →
`<ChapterIndex>` (the four chapters) → footer CTA. It is NOT a long scroll of
every section — chapter depth lives on the routes above. Each chapter page ends
with a `<ChapterPager>` to the next chapter.

## 7. Performance & accessibility checklist (apply every task)

- Lazy-load all 3D / R3F (`React.lazy` + `Suspense`); never block first paint.
- Cap dye/sim resolution per device; provide a static fallback for weak GPUs and
  WebGL-unavailable cases (see hero's `is-fallback`).
- Honor `prefers-reduced-motion` everywhere (scroll, reveals, parallax, 3D).
- Animate only `transform`/`opacity`/`filter`; avoid layout thrash; use
  `will-change` sparingly; kill/cleanup ScrollTriggers and Lenis on unmount.
- Every section must visibly belong to Meniscus (glass + depth + viscous motion).
  If a section looks like it could be a different template, it's wrong.

## 8. The Fish — ambient companion (reserved, build later)

A small animated fish swims in the water layer *beneath the glass* — the living
detail that rewards exploration. Mechanic: **"feed the fish to browse more"** —
interacting with it (dropping food/ink) nudges the visitor onward and reveals
more of the site, keeping the experience playful and interactive. Primary home:
the Lab (`/projects`), but architected to swim in any water surface.

Status: **the owner builds the animation later.** For now, reserve a clearly-
marked, stable mount slot in the water layer (a `<FishCompanion>` placeholder,
same pattern as the route-hero placeholders) so it drops in cleanly. Do NOT
build the fish now — just leave the seam.

## 9. Landing hero — interaction rules

- **Ink swatch = hover, not click.** Moving the pointer over a swatch switches
  the active ink immediately (`pointerenter`); previously-laid ink stays and
  accumulates. Keep click/tap (touch has no hover) and keyboard focus as
  equivalent selectors — never hover-only, or touch + keyboard users can't pick.
- **Ink lingers longer before fading.** Lever: `densityDissipation` in
  `src/hero/fluid/inkConfig.ts` (lower = lingers longer). Tune down from `0.1`
  toward `~0.045`; do NOT reach `0` (muddy brown build-up + sim instability).
  Keep it the single tunable for ink persistence.
